The best part is the ability to organise all the different notes (files) into different folders that you have created for yourself - whereas with some other notes apps you don't get that option, so similar themed notes don't get grouped together & can get lost among the other notes (not of the same theme) - especially if you happen to write lots of notes as I happen to do !    The option to encrypt each note with a different password is also great, especially if writing up within the note sensitive/confidential info. that you don't want anyone to look at, especially should the PC Tablet get lost or stolen.    Although there is no master password feature that you can use to entirely lock the app (ie. one that gets you to enter f/ex. a 4-digit pin before you can access/open the app) you can always download any of the free application lock apps that are are available from the Google Play Store to give you that added security protection of your Note Everything (with Pro Add-on) app.    The best thing about this app is its simplicity - just plain lined pages per note, no annoying background picture clutter, no silly fonts, no nonsense really. *Note to other users. This is an add-on, you don't open it, it just opens up new options in the free version.  I absolutely chose this note app for two main reasons. First off, well it's just a beautiful, feature-filled, note taking app. That easily rivals if not trumps any other note app available on the Market! Second and most important to me is the permissions. I can't trust my private notes to just any application, but with Note Everything, and now having the Pro version with the added encryption settings, well I'm way more happy using this app. And the developer doesn't add a whole cornucopia of dangerous and suspect permissions like Discover Known Accounts, Read Sensitive Log Data, and most importantly does not request Internet Access. So I feel extremely safe knowing the contents of my notes won't be offloaded to a server somewhere. The day this app requests anything like those permissions is the day I immediately uninstall it and find a new one. But I have faith that the dev will keep doing what they do best, and maintain an awesome and secure note app! Money easily well spent for a peace of mind, thank you so much! I was a hardcore Palm Desktop user (11 years), & I am *very picky* with my Note-taking...  ...& Note Everything Pro DOES IT ALL, & then Some: *tons of folders, & subfolder hierarchies {Palm restricted to 16 subfolders) *Massive Note size {Palm restricted to 32k} *Insert date+time-stamp (Crucial for taking Journal entries, etc) *Dynamic Search: search as you type, Google-like search-results (ie, shows search keyword in context), -&- search keyword(s) are highlighted in the Note when you open it...No more hunting around! *very flexible display options, from Font Size, background color, to even header button inclusion & ordering!  *NE Gdoc: sync a Note to the cloud for File Sharing, desktop editing *NE Push: allows auto-create a Note from typing in a browser!  ...the combo of these two is 'almost' a full Desktop Editing solution... *File Backup: Use 'Automatic Backups', & then use 'Real Sync' or 'DropSpace' (auto cloud backups), or 'Dropbox' app! (manual) *Shortcuts to desktop, Notification 'Sticky' Note *Encrypted Notes, Reminder Notes, Checklists/Durable ...even 'swap Context menu for 10seconds" is raaad.   This is the BEST, Bar None... And at $5, it's a STEAL.
